description: EulerPhi(n) has more prime factors than n.
example: All primes except Fermat-primes are included. Also true prime powers are included, such as 289 because Phi(289)=17.16=272 with 2 prime divisors. Besides many composites are included like 998=2.499 because Phi(998)=498-2.3.83 with 3>2 prime-factors.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Jul 11 2000
